  "denoised_question": "<denoised_question>Let n be a positive integer. A child builds a wall along a line with prime n identical cubes. He lays the first cube on the line and at each subsequent step, he lays the next cube either on the ground or on the top of another cube, so that it has a common face with the previous one. How many such distinct walls exist?</denoised_question>",
